Reasoning: The paper discusses the Lexicographic Breadth First Search (LBFS) algorithm and its applications in various graph classes, including chordal graphs, split graphs, interval graphs, and asteroidal triple-free (AT-free) graphs. These topics are closely related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM), data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), graph theory (cs.GT), and machine learning (cs.DL). However, since the paper focuses on graph algorithms and their complexity, cs.DM and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CG and cs.GT. cs.DL is less likely since it is not directly related to the topic of the paper.
